# Enzo Chatbot

Enzo is a web-based chatbot designed to manage and answer WhatsApp chats. It utilizes AI to provide quick and accurate responses, enhancing user interaction and experience.

![Enzo Logo](/frontend/assets/bot-icon.png) <!-- Update the path to your logo -->

## Table of Contents
- [Features](#features)
- [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)
- [Setup Instructions](#setup-instructions)
- [How to Use](#how-to-use)
- [License](#license)
- [Code of Conduct](#code-of-conduct)
- [Contact Information](#contact-information)

## Features
- AI-driven responses similar to ChatGPT.
- User-friendly interface.
- Easy integration with WhatsApp.
- Customizable settings for personal user experience.

## Technologies Used
- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript
- Node.js (for backend)
- Express.js
- OpenAI API (for AI responses)

## Setup Instructions

### Prerequisites
- Node.js installed on your machine.
- Access to OpenAI API keys.

### Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/enzo-chatbot.git
cd enzo-chatbot

Install Dependencies

bash

npm install

Configure Environment Variables
Create a .env file in the root directory and add your OpenAI API key:

makefile

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
Run the Application

bash

node server.js
Access the Chatbot
Open your browser and go to http://localhost:5500 to start using Enzo.

How to Use
Type your message in the input field.
Click the send button or press Enter to send your message.
Enzo will respond based on the input you provided.
